==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypodermic
<hw>Hyp`o*der"mic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Hypoderma</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the parts under the
skin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hypodermic medication</b></col>, <cd>the application of
remedies under the epidermis, usually by means of a small syringe,
called the hypodermic syringe.</cd></cs></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Hyp`o*der"mic*al*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hypodermic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: hypodermic
<hw>hyp`o*der"mic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A <er>hypodermic
needle</er>{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypodermic needle</ent>⟦br⟧
